# WeaveFFI Wasm (experimental)

This folder contains a minimal stub to help you load a `wasm32-unknown-unknown` build of your WeaveFFI library.

Build (example):

```bash
cargo build --target wasm32-unknown-unknown --release
```

Then serve the `.wasm` and use `weaveffi_wasm.js` to load it.

## Complex Type Handling

Wasm only supports numeric types natively (`i32`, `i64`, `f32`, `f64`). Complex types are encoded at the boundary as follows:

### Structs

Structs are passed as **opaque handles** (`i64` pointers into linear memory). The host cannot inspect struct fields directly; use the generated accessor functions (`weaveffi_{module}_{struct}_get_{field}`) to read/write fields. A returned struct handle is owned by the consumer; the JS wrapper's `free()` releases it via the struct's `_destroy` symbol.

### Enums

Enums are passed as **`i32` values** corresponding to the variant's integer discriminant.

### Optionals

Optional values use **`0` / `null`** to represent the absent case. Scalar optionals are boxed by pointer (a null pointer signals absence); handle-typed and string optionals pass a null pointer (`0`) directly.

### Lists

Lists are passed as a **pointer + length** pair (`i32` pointer, `i32` length) referencing a contiguous region in linear memory. The caller is responsible for allocating and freeing the backing memory.

### Iterators

`iter<T>` functions return a **lazy JS iterator** (typed `IterableIterator<T>`): each `next()` issues exactly one producer call, so iteration streams in constant memory. The producer handle is destroyed exactly once, on exhaustion or via `return()` when iteration stops early (a `for...of` loop calls `return()` automatically on `break` or `throw`). Abandoning an iterator without exhausting or closing it leaks the handle.

### Callbacks and Listeners

Each listener surfaces as a `register.../unregister...` pair. `register` takes a plain JS function and returns a numeric subscription id; `unregister` takes that id and stops delivery. Delivery is **synchronous and same-thread**: `wasm32-unknown-unknown` is single-threaded, so events fire only while a call into the module is on the stack (for example, a producer function that emits during its own execution). A producer that emits from a spawned thread cannot run on this target at all.

Callback arguments are **borrowed for the duration of the callback**: strings and byte buffers are copied into JS values before your function runs, but struct, rich-enum, and interface arguments wrap producer-owned memory. Read what you need inside the callback and do not retain the wrapper or call `free()` on it.

### Error Handling

The generated JS wrappers automatically handle errors by passing an error
pointer as the last argument to each Wasm function. Your Wasm module must
export the following functions:

- `weaveffi_alloc(size: i32) -> i32`: allocate `size` bytes in linear memory
- `weaveffi_dealloc(ptr: i32, size: i32)`: release a `weaveffi_alloc` block
- `weaveffi_error_clear(err_ptr: i32)`: clear and free error resources
- `weaveffi_free_string(ptr: i32)`: free a producer-returned C string
- `weaveffi_free_bytes(ptr: i32, len: i32)`: free a producer-returned buffer

Wrappers of functions declared `throws` raise the declaring module's typed
error class (a `WeaveFFIError` subclass with a per-code subclass, such as
`KeyNotFound`); every other wrapper raises the generic `WeaveFFIError` only
for producer panics and marshalling failures.

## API Reference

### Module: `docs`

#### Error Domain: `DocsErrorsError`

Throwing wrappers in this module raise `DocsErrorsError` (a `WeaveFFIError` subclass); each code below is its own subclass carrying the stable `code`.

| Class | Code | Default Message |
|-------|------|-----------------|
| `NotFound` | `1` | Document not found |
| `InvalidStatus` | `2` | Invalid status transition |

#### Functions

##### `weaveffi_docs_create_document`

Create a brand new document.

The document starts in `Draft` status; callers must publish
it explicitly to make it visible.


`weaveffi_docs_create_document(title: i32, i32, tags: i32, i32) -> i64`

| Param | API Type | Wasm | Notes |
|-------|----------|------|-------|
| `title` | `string` | `i32, i32` | ptr + len in linear memory |
| `tags` | `[string]` | `i32, i32` | ptr + len in linear memory |
| _returns_ | `Document` | `i64` | opaque handle in linear memory |

##### `weaveffi_docs_get_document`

Look up a document by identifier

`weaveffi_docs_get_document(id: i64) -> i64`

| Param | API Type | Wasm | Notes |
|-------|----------|------|-------|
| `id` | `i64` | `i64` | native Wasm i64 |
| _returns_ | `Document?` | `i64` | opaque handle, 0 = absent |

##### `weaveffi_docs_publish_async`

Publish a document in the background

`weaveffi_docs_publish_async(id: i64) -> i32`

| Param | API Type | Wasm | Notes |
|-------|----------|------|-------|
| `id` | `i64` | `i64` | native Wasm i64 |
| _returns_ | `bool` | `i32` | 0 = false, 1 = true |

#### Interfaces

##### `Notebook`

An ordered collection of documents.

Notebooks own their documents and release them when destroyed.


Passed as an **opaque handle** (`i64`), wrapped by a JS class. Constructors return an owned handle; methods pass the handle as the implicit leading `self` argument; `free()` releases the handle via the destroy symbol.

##### `weaveffi_docs_Notebook_new`

Create an empty notebook

`weaveffi_docs_Notebook_new() -> i64`

| Param | API Type | Wasm | Notes |
|-------|----------|------|-------|
| _returns_ | `Notebook` | `i64` | opaque handle in linear memory |

##### `weaveffi_docs_Notebook_insert`

Add a document, returning its position in the notebook

`weaveffi_docs_Notebook_insert(document: i64) -> i32`

| Param | API Type | Wasm | Notes |
|-------|----------|------|-------|
| `document` | `Document` | `i64` | opaque handle in linear memory |
| _returns_ | `i32` | `i32` | native Wasm i32 |

##### `weaveffi_docs_Notebook_find`

Look up a document by identifier, failing when none matches

`weaveffi_docs_Notebook_find(id: i64) -> i64`

| Param | API Type | Wasm | Notes |
|-------|----------|------|-------|
| `id` | `i64` | `i64` | native Wasm i64 |
| _returns_ | `Document` | `i64` | opaque handle in linear memory |

##### `weaveffi_docs_Notebook_size`

The number of documents currently held

`weaveffi_docs_Notebook_size() -> i32`

| Param | API Type | Wasm | Notes |
|-------|----------|------|-------|
| _returns_ | `i32` | `i32` | native Wasm i32 |

##### `weaveffi_docs_Notebook_max_documents`

The largest number of documents one notebook will hold

`weaveffi_docs_Notebook_max_documents() -> i32`

| Param | API Type | Wasm | Notes |
|-------|----------|------|-------|
| _returns_ | `i32` | `i32` | native Wasm i32 |

##### `weaveffi_docs_Notebook_destroy`

Releases the object reference. Called by the wrapper's `free()`.

#### Structs

##### `Document`

Represents a single document tracked by the system.

Documents are persisted to disk and exposed via the public API.


Passed as opaque handle (`i64`).

| Accessor | Wasm Return |
|----------|-------------|
| `weaveffi_docs_Document_get_id` | `i64` |
| `weaveffi_docs_Document_get_title` | `i32, i32` |
| `weaveffi_docs_Document_get_status` | `i32` |
| `weaveffi_docs_Document_get_tags` | `i32, i32` |

##### `DocumentBuilder`

Builder for `Document`.

| Function | Args | Return |
|----------|------|--------|
| `weaveffi_docs_Document_Builder_new` | none | `i32` (handle) |
| `weaveffi_docs_Document_Builder_set_id` | `i32` handle, `i64` value | none |
| `weaveffi_docs_Document_Builder_set_title` | `i32` handle, `i32, i32` value | none |
| `weaveffi_docs_Document_Builder_set_status` | `i32` handle, `i32` value | none |
| `weaveffi_docs_Document_Builder_set_tags` | `i32` handle, `i32, i32` value | none |
| `weaveffi_docs_Document_Builder_build` | `i32` handle | `i32` (handle) |
| `weaveffi_docs_Document_Builder_destroy` | `i32` handle | none |

#### Enums

##### `Status`

Lifecycle status of a document.

Used to drive UI badges and filters.


Passed as `i32` discriminant.

| Variant | Value |
|---------|-------|
| `Draft` | `0` |
| `Published` | `1` |
| `Archived` | `2` |

